name: Acetaldehyde air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)
description: This map estimates ambient concentration (microgram/m3) of acetaldehyde from the National Air Toxics Assessment.

name: Acetaldehyde air toxics - Cancer risk per million
description: This map estimates cancer risk per million due to acetaldehyde air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. Cancer risk is defined as the probability of contracting cancer over the course of a lifetime, assuming continuous exposure (assumed in NATA to be 70 years).
ViewName: Acetaldehyde air toxics - Cancer risk per million

name: Acetaldehyde air toxics - Respiratory risk (hazard quotient)
description: This map estimates non-cancer respiratory risk (hazard quotient) due to acetaldehyde air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. A hazard quotient is defined as the ratio of the potential exposure to the substance and the level at which no adverse effects are expected. A hazard quotient less than or equal to one indicates that adverse noncancer effects are not likely to occur, and thus can be considered to have negligible hazard.
ViewName: Acetaldehyde air toxics - Respiratory risk (hazard quotient)

name: Acres of land enrolled in CRP
description: This map portrays the acres of land within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that are enrolled in the US Department of Agriculture's Conservation Reserve Program (CRP). The CRP is a program administered by the Farm Service Agency; farmers in the program receive annual payments and establishment cost share to remove environmentally sensitive land from crop production and instead plant perennial species that provide environmental benefits.
ViewName: Acres of land enrolled in CRP

name: Acres of pollinated crops with no nearby pollinator habitat
description: This map layer depicts the total acres of agricultural crops within a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that require or would benefit from the presence of pollinators, but are without any nearby supporting habitat for 2006-2010.
ViewName: Acres of pollinated crops with no nearby pollinator habitat

name: Acrolein air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)
description: This map estimates ambient concentration (microgram/m3) of acrolein from the National Air Toxics Assessment.

name: Acrolein air toxics - Respiratory risk (hazard quotient)
description: This map estimates non-cancer respiratory risk (hazard quotient) due to acrolein air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. A hazard quotient is defined as the ratio of the potential exposure to the substance and the level at which no adverse effects are expected. A hazard quotient less than or equal to one indicates that adverse noncancer effects are not likely to occur, and thus can be considered to have negligible hazard.
ViewName: Acrolein air toxics - Respiratory risk (hazard quotient)

name: Acute respiratory symptoms avoided due to ozone removed by tree cover (cases/yr)
description: This map estimates the annual number of acute respiratory symptom cases that may be avoided due to total ozone removed by trees in each census block group.

name: Acute respiratory symptoms avoided due to particulate matter [PM2.5] removed by tree cover (cases/yr)
description: This map estimates the annual number of acute respiratory symptom cases that may be avoided due to total PM2.5 removed by trees in each census block group.

name: Agricultural land per capita (m2/person)
description: This map estimates the square meters of land per person that is managed for agriculture within each census block group.

name: Agricultural water use (million gallons/day)
description: This map estimates the millions of gallons of water used daily for agricultural irrigation for each subwatershed (HUC-12) in the contiguous United States for 2007-2012. Estimates include self-supplied surface and groundwater, as well as water supplied by irrigation water providers, which may include governments, companies, or other organizations.

name: Air Quality System (AIRS AQS)
description: The Air Quality System (AQS) contains ambient air pollution data collected by EPA, State, Local, and Tribal air pollution control agencies from thousands of monitoring stations. Updated regularly, typically at least quarterly.

name: All cattle - Number of heads
description: This map shows the number of heads of all cattle on operations at the end of 2017 by county.

name: All cattle - Number of operations
description: This map shows the number of operations with any type of cattle on their property at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Annual oxidized nitrogen dry deposition (kg/ha)
description: This map estimates the annual dry deposition of oxidized nitrogen within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kilograms per hectare for 2016. Dry deposition occurs when particles or gases attach to surfaces such as dust or smoke and fall to the earth's surface.

name: Annual oxidized nitrogen wet deposition (kg/ha)
description: This map estimates the annual wet deposition of oxidized nitrogen within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kilograms per hectare for 2016. Wet deposition occurs when rain, snow, or fog carry nitrogen to the earth’s surface.

name: Annual reduced nitrogen dry deposition (kg/ha)
description: This map estimates the annual dry deposition of reduced nitrogen within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kilograms per hectare for 2016. Dry deposition occurs when particles or gases attach to surfaces such as dust or smoke and fall to the earth's surface.

name: Annual reduced nitrogen wet deposition (kg/ha)
description: This map estimates the annual wet deposition of reduced nitrogen within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kilograms per hectare for 2016. Wet deposition occurs when rain, snow, or fog carry nitrogen to the earth’s surface.

name: Annual sulfur dry deposition (kg/ha)
description: This map estimates the annual dry deposition of sulfur within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kilograms per hectare for 2016. Dry deposition occurs when particles or gases attach to surfaces such as dust or smoke and fall to the earth's surface.

name: Annual sulfur wet deposition (kg/ha)
description: This map estimates the annual wet deposition of sulfur within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kilograms per hectare for 2016. Wet deposition occurs when rain, snow, or fog carry sulfur to the earth’s surface.

name: Area in square meters of estimated floodplain classified as water
description: This map shows the area in square meters of estimated floodplain classified as water within the subwatershed (12-digit HUC).
ViewName: Area in square meters of estimated floodplain classified as water

name: Area of estimated floodplain classified as land (m2)
description: This map shows the area in square meters of estimated floodplain classified as land within the subwatershed (12-digit HUC).
ViewName: Area of estimated floodplain classified as land (m2)

name: Area of solar energy (km2)
description: This map estimates the square kilometers of area within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that offers the potential for harvesting solar energy for 2009. This map does not take into account land use or ownership.

name: Arsenic air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)
description: This map estimates ambient concentration (microgram/m3) of arsenic from the National Air Toxics Assessment.

name: Arsenic air toxics - Cancer risk per million
description: This map estimates cancer risk per million due to arsenic air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. Cancer risk is defined as the probability of contracting cancer over the course of a lifetime, assuming continuous exposure (assumed in NATA to be 70 years).
ViewName: Arsenic air toxics - Cancer risk per million

name: Assessed and Impaired Water Areas
description: This map depicts waterbodies assessed to evaluate waterbody condition for seven beneficial uses (such as aquatic life habitat, drinking water supply, and fish consumption) every two years by states, territories, and authorized tribes. Those waterbodies not meeting the standards for beneficial uses are designated as impaired or threatened. This map identifies area features from the Assessed Waters database.

name: Assessed and Impaired Water Catchment Associations
description: This map depicts waterbodies assessed to evaluate waterbody condition for seven beneficial uses (such as aquatic life habitat, drinking water supply, and fish consumption) every two years by states, territories, and authorized tribes. Those waterbodies not meeting the standards for beneficial uses are designated as impaired or threatened. This map identifies Catchment Associations from the Assessed Waters database.

name: Assessed and Impaired Water Lines
description: This map depicts waterbodies assessed to evaluate waterbody condition for seven beneficial uses (such as aquatic life habitat, drinking water supply, and fish consumption) every two years by states, territories, and authorized tribes. Those waterbodies not meeting the standards for beneficial uses are designated as impaired or threatened. This map identifies linear features from the Assessed Waters database.

name: Assessed and Impaired Water Points
description: This map depicts waterbodies assessed to evaluate waterbody condition for seven beneficial uses (such as aquatic life habitat, drinking water supply, and fish consumption) every two years by states, territories, and authorized tribes. Those waterbodies not meeting the standards for beneficial uses are designated as impaired or threatened. This map identifies point features from the Assessed Waters database.

name: Asthma exacerbation avoided due to nitrogen dioxide removed by tree cover (cases/yr)
description: This map estimates the annual number of asthma exacerbation cases that may be avoided due to total nitrogen dioxide removed by trees in each census block group.

name: Asthma exacerbation avoided due to sulfur dioxide removed by tree cover (cases/yr)
description: This map estimates the annual number of asthma exacerbation cases that may be avoided due to total sulfur dioxide removed by trees in each census block group.

name: Average annual daily potential solar energy (kWh/m2/day)
description: This map estimates the average daily potential kilowatt hours of solar energy that could be harvested per square meter within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2009. This calculation is based on environmental factors and does not take into account land ownership or viability of installing solar harvesting systems.
ViewName: Average annual daily potential solar energy (kWh/m2/day)

name: Average annual daily potential wind energy (kWh/m2/day)
description: This map estimates the average daily potential kilowatt hours of wind energy that could be harvested per square meter within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC), based on data from 2001-2012. This calculation is based on environmental factors and does not take into account land ownership or viability of installing wind harvesting systems.
ViewName: Average annual daily potential wind energy (kWh/m2/day)

name: Average annual precipitation (inches/yr)
description: This map estimates the average number of inches of precipitation that fall within a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) each year. Precipitation includes snow and rain accumulation.

name: Average reduction in daytime ambient temperature (Celsius)
description: This map estimates the average reduction in the ambient temperature at 2pm on a hot summer day due to the cooling properties of tree cover in each census block group.

name: Average reduction in nighttime ambient temperature (Celsius)
description: This map estimates the average reduction in the ambient temperature at night following a hot summer day due to the cooling properties of tree cover in each census block group.

name: Average width of stream buffers downstream from agriculture (meters)
description: The average width in meters of buffers that are contiguous to the stream and are intersected by agricultural flow paths. This metric does not include any riparian areas that do not also contain agriculture upslope.
ViewName: Average width of stream buffers downstream from agriculture (meters)

name: Beef cattle - Number of heads
description: This map shows the number of heads of beef cattle on operations at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Beef cattle - Number of operations
description: This map shows the number of operations with beef cattle on their property at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Broiler chickens - Number of heads

name: Broiler chickens - Number of operations
description: This map shows the number of operations that sold broiler chickens during 2017 by county.

name: Brownfield Properties (ACRES)
description: This dataset includes data from facilities reporting to EPA - Brownfields: Shows only points from the Assessment, Cleanup and Redevelopment Exchange System (ACRES) grantee reported data on environmental activities and accomplishments (assessment, cleanup and redevelopment), funding, job training, and details on cooperative partners and leveraging efforts - a central objective of the Brownfields Program. Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: Business address vacancy rate for 2014
description: This map displays the percentage of business addresses that had remained vacant for more than one year in 2014. This layer is based on the United States Postal Service (USPS) Vacant Address Data.

name: Butadiene air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)

name: Candidate Ecological Restoration Areas
description: These polygons represent candidate areas for ecological restoration, based on potential to improve connectivity between naturally vegetated areas.

name: Candidate Ecological Restoration Areas per square kilometer
description: This map depicts the number of Candidate Ecological Restoration Areas (CERAs) per square kilometer. CERAs are areas that could be restored to connect large vegetated areas. They were identified using morphological spatial pattern analysis.

name: Carbon monoxide removed annually by tree cover (kg/yr)

name: Change in business vacancy rate from 2010-2014, in percentage points

name: Change in residential vacancy rate from 2010-2014, in percentage points
description: This map displays the change in the residential vacancy rate from 2010-2014 in percentage points (2014 rate minus 2010 rate). This layer is based on the United States Postal Service (USPS) Vacant Address Data. Vacant buildings are included if they remained vacant for more than one year.
ViewName: Change in residential vacancy rate from 2010-2014, in percentage points

name: Cotton yields (thousand tons/yr)
description: This map depicts the thousands of tons of cotton that are grown annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2007-2010.

name: Crop phosphorus removal (kg P/ha/yr)
description: This map estimates the mean crop phosphorus (P) removal from croplands in kilograms P per hectare per year within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2012.

name: Cultivated biological nitrogen fixation (kg N/ha/yr)
description: This map depicts the mean rate of biological nitrogen fixation from the cultivation of crops within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kg N/ha/yr for 2006.

name: Cyanobacteria Index - Extent
description: This map shows the average annual spatial extent of cyanobacterial blooms detected by satellite for over 2,000 freshwater lakes in the conterminous US. The results range from 0 to 100 where 0 indicates a cyanobacterial bloom was never detected by the satellite sensor for any pixels across all satellite images considered within the lake boundary and 100 indicates a cyanobacterial bloom was detected by the satellite sensor for all pixels across all satellite images considered within the lake boundary.

name: Cyanobacteria Index - Frequency
description: This map shows the average annual temporal frequency of cyanobacterial blooms detected by satellite for over 2,000 freshwater lakes in the conterminous US. The results range from 0 to 100 where 0 indicates a cyanobacterial bloom was never detected by the satellite sensor for any pixels across all satellite images considered within the lake boundary and 100 indicates a cyanobacterial bloom was detected by the satellite sensor for all pixels across all satellite images considered within the lake boundary.

name: Daily domestic water use (x1000 gal/day)
description: This map estimates the total water used daily for domestic purposes in each census block group. For the purposes of this map, domestic or residential water use includes all indoor and outdoor uses, such as for drinking, bathing, cleaning, landscaping, and pools for primary residences

name: Dairy cattle - Number of heads
description: This map shows the number of heads of dairy cattle on operations at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Dairy cattle - Number of operations
description: This map shows the number of operations with dairy cattle on their property at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Dasymetric allocation of population 2010 CONUS
description: This dasymetric population map intelligently reallocates 2010 population from census blocks to 30 meter pixels based on land cover and slope. It is used for metrics that require population to be spatially allocated at a pixel level, primarily in the urban section of the atlas.

name: Dasymetric allocation of population 2020 CONUS
description: This dasymetric population map intelligently reallocates 2020 population from census blocks to 30 meter pixels based on land cover and slope. It is used for metrics that require population to be spatially allocated at a pixel level, primarily in the urban section of the atlas.

name: Day care centers with < 25 percent green space in viewshed
description: This map summarizes the number of day care centers in each census block group that have less than 25 percent of “green space” in the area within 100 meters of the building.  Green space may include trees, lawns and gardens, crop land, and forested wetlands.

name: Diesel PM air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)
description: This map estimates ambient concentration (microgram/m3) of diesel PM from the National Air Toxics Assessment.
ViewName: Diesel PM air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)

description: This map estimates non-cancer respiratory risk (hazard quotient) due to diesel PM air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. A hazard quotient is defined as the ratio of the potential exposure to the substance and the level at which no adverse effects are expected. A hazard quotient less than or equal to one indicates that adverse noncancer effects are not likely to occur, and thus can be considered to have negligible hazard.
ViewName: Diesel PM air toxics - Respiratory risk (hazard quotient)

name: Dissolved nitrogen in non-tile drain subsurface flow from agricultural fields (tons)
description: This map provides modeled estimates of the movement (flux) of nitrogen dissolved in sub-surface (lateral) flow at the outer edges of non-tile drained agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of N for 2002. It includes nitogen from fertilizer application and atmospheric deposition.
ViewName: Dissolved nitrogen in non-tile drain subsurface flow from agricultural fields (tons)

name: Dissolved nutrients in leachate from agricultural fields (tons) Nitrogen
description: This map provides modeled estimates of nitrogen leachate, i.e., mass of nitrogen dissolved in percolate moving downward out of the soil layer underlying agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of N for 2002. It does not necessarily reflect the amount of nitrogen that actually enters an underlying groundwater reservoir.
ViewName: Dissolved nutrients in leachate from agricultural fields (tons) Nitrogen

name: Dissolved nutrients in leachate from agricultural fields (tons) Phosphorus
description: This map provides modeled estimates of phosphorus leachate, i.e., mass of phosphorus dissolved in percolate moving downward out of the soil layer underlying agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of P for 2002. It does not necessarily reflect the amount of nitrogen that actually enters an underlying groundwater reservoir.
ViewName: Dissolved nutrients in leachate from agricultural fields (tons) Phosphorus

name: Dissolved nutrients in surface runoff from agricultural fields (tons) Nitrogen
description: This map provides modeled estimates of the movement (flux) of nitrogen dissolved in surface runoff at the outer edges of all agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of N for 2002. It includes nitogen from fertilizer application and atmospheric deposition.
ViewName: Dissolved nutrients in surface runoff from agricultural fields (tons) Nitrogen

name: Dissolved nutrients in surface runoff from agricultural fields (tons) Phosphorus
description: This map provides modeled estimates of the movement (flux) of phosphorus dissolved in surface runoff at the outer edges of all agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of P for 2002. It includes phosphorus from fertilizer application and atmospheric deposition.
ViewName: Dissolved nutrients in surface runoff from agricultural fields (tons) Phosphorus

name: Dissolved nutrients in tile drain subsurface flow from agricultural fields (tons) Nitrogen
description: This map provides modeled estimates of the movement (flux) of nitrogen dissolved in sub-surface (lateral) flow at the outer edges of tile drained agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of N for 2002. It includes nitogen from fertilizer application and atmospheric deposition.
ViewName: Dissolved nutrients in tile drain subsurface flow from agricultural fields (tons) Nitrogen

name: Dissolved nutrients in tile drain subsurface flow from agricultural fields (tons) Phosphorus
description: This map provides modeled estimates of the movement (flux) of phosphorus dissolved in sub-surface (lateral) flow at the outer edges of tile-drained agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of P for 2002. It includes phosphorus from fertilizer application and atmospheric deposition.
ViewName: Dissolved nutrients in tile drain subsurface flow from agricultural fields (tons) Phosphorus

name: Domestic water use (million gallons/day)
description: This map estimates the millions of gallons of water used daily for domestic purposes in each subwatershed (HUC-12) for 2010-2011. For the purposes of this map, domestic or residential water use includes all indoor and outdoor uses, such as for drinking, bathing, cleaning, landscaping, and pools for primary residences.

name: Ducks - Number of heads
description: This map shows the number of heads of ducks on operations at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Ducks - Number of operations
description: This map shows the number of operations with ducks on their property at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Ecological integrity of stream confluence catchments and watersheds
description: This map depicts the results of a cluster analysis of stream confluences – locations where two or more streams meet – using ecological integrity indices for local catchments and contributing watersheds from the StreamCat database. The index of catchment integrity (ICI) and index of watershed integrity (IWI) are based on a stream's water chemistry, sediment load, hydrologic connectivity, habitat provision, and capacity to regulate stream temperature. Clusters are labeled poor (ICI or IWI < 0.35), moderate (mean ICI and IWI values ≥0.35 and <0.60), good (ICI and IWI ≥ 0.60), or contrast (markedly contrasting ecological conditions between mainstem and tributary, local catchment and contributing watershed, or both).

name: Employment density (jobs/ac)
description: This map estimates employment density (or jobs per acre) within each census block group. Developed acreage is calculated by excluding parks, water bodies, conservation easements, and other protected areas.

name: Employment diversity
description: This map portrays a measure of employment diversity within each census block group. Job counts used in the equation are from eight employment categories: retail, office, service, industrial, entertainment, education, healthcare, and public administration.

name: Employment Rate (percent)
description: This map estimates the percent of the population aged 16-64 who have worked in the past 12 months by block group. It includes people who worked any number of hours per week.  The data are based on the American Community Survey 5-year data for 2008-2012.

name: Employment:housing ratio
description: This map estimates the jobs-to-housing balance (or total employment divided by total occupied housing units) within each census block group for 2010.

name: Enabling Conditions
description: This dataset contains polygons representing guidance, enabling policies, and regulatory drivers that facilitate ecosystem services markets per Ecosystem Marketplace research. It includes conditions that specifically establish ecosystem market mechanisms, as well as conditions that indirectly function as the regulatory driver for ecosystem markets. Data cover watershed, Imperiled Species and Habitats, wetland and streams, and forest carbon asset types. Scales represented include watershed (HUC8), state, regional, national, and federal lands.

name: EnviroAtlas Community Boundaries
description: EnviroAtlas Communities and vicinities. The EnviroAtlas boundary for the each Community area was determined using the 2010 Census definition of an Urban Area.

name: EPA and BLM Tribal Areas - Alaska Native Allotments
description: This map depicts Alaska Native Allotment parcels from the Bureau of Land Management.

name: EPA and BLM Tribal Areas - Alaska Native Villages
description: This map depicts Alaska Native Villages, presented as boundary centroid points based on selected and conveyed land boundaries provided by the Bureau of Land Management Alaska State Office. The Alaska Native Villages are associated with Federally recognized tribal entities based on the Agency’s current interpretation of the EPA 1984 Indian Policy per EPA’s American Indian Environmental Office (AIEO). Under the Alaska Native Claims Settlement Act (ANCSA) of 1971, specific regional or village corporations can select federal lands within their legally defined regions to be conveyed to them.

name: EPA and USCB Tribal Areas - American Indian Off-Reservation Trust Lands
description: This map depicts American Indian Off-Reservation Trust Land areas  –  areas for which the United States holds title in trust for the benefit of a tribe or for an individual American Indian – in the lower 48 states from the U.S. Census Bureau with data fields enhanced by the EPA. The areas include all Off-Reservation Trust Lands associated with Federally recognized tribal entities.

name: EPA and USCB Tribal Areas - American Indian Reservations
description: This map depicts American Indian Reservations (AIRs) from the Census Bureau in the lower 48 states and Alaska. AIRs are areas set aside by the federal government for use by tribes.

name: EPA and USCB Tribal Areas - Oklahoma Tribal Statistical Areas
description: This map depicts Oklahoma Statistical Areas (OTSAs). OTSA Joint-Use Areas, as applied to OTSAs by the Census Bureau, include areas administered jointly and/or claimed by two or more American Indian tribes that have a delineated OTSA. Note that due to a recent Supreme Court decision, Oklahoma Indian country boundaries are in a state of flux.

name: EPA and USCB Tribal Areas - Virginia Federally Recognized Tribes
description: Virginia Federally Recognized Tribes contains point data for tribes geographically located in the state of Virginia, corresponding with the administrative boundaries of EPA Region 3. These tribes are federally recognized, but do not currently have land in federal status. Locations are based on mailing addresses for each tribe.

name: Estimated floodplains
description: This map depicts the estimated 100-year floodplains for the Conterminous US for 2016.

name: Estimated intersection density of walkable roads per km2
description: This EnviroAtlas dataset estimates the intersection density of walkable roads within a 750 meter radius of any given 10 meter pixel in the community. Intersections are defined as any point where 3 or more roads meet and density is calculated using kernel density, where closer intersections are weighted higher than further intersections. Intersection density is highly correlated with walking for transportation.

name: Estimated percent of tree cover within 26m of a road edge
description: This map estimates the percent tree cover within 26 meters of a busy road edge at any given point throughout the community. A “busy” roadway in EnviroAtlas is defined to include interstates, arterial roads, and collector roads. It does not include local or neighborhood roads, though some of these roads may also experience consistent and heavy traffic.

name: Estimated tree cover in 15m stream and lake buffer (percent)
description: This map estimates the percent tree cover within 15 meters of hydrologically connected non-coastal waters. It is not summarized by census block group.

name: Estimated tree cover in 50m stream and lake buffer (percent)
description: This map estimates the percent tree cover within 50 meters of hydrologically connected non-coastal waters. It is not summarized by census block group.

name: Estimated vegetated cover in 15m stream and lake buffer (percent)
description: This map estimates the percent vegetated cover within 15 meters of hydrologically connected non-coastal waters. It is not summarized by census block group.

name: Estimated vegetated cover in 50m stream and lake buffer (percent)
description: This map estimates the percent vegetated cover within 50 meters of hydrologically connected non-coastal waters. It is not summarized by census block group.

name: Estimated walking distance to a park entrance (m)
description: This map estimates the total meters, or walking distance, from each park entrance.

name: Forest Carbon - Projects and Markets
description: This dataset contains polygons and points representing the location of markets and projects primarily targeting forest carbon-related ecosystem services per Ecosystem Marketplace research. Polygons for projects represent the area of primary impact. Polygons for markets represent the entire region that shares market infrastructure and rules, or a larger program encompassing many smaller projects. Points represent the centroids of forest carbon markets and lat/lon locations of forest carbon projects with the exception of national markets, whose points represent administrative headquarters locations.

name: Formaldehyde air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)
description: This map estimates ambient concentration (microgram/m3) of formaldehyde from the National Air Toxics Assessment.

name: Freshwater fishing recreation demand (day trips per year)

name: Fruit yields (thousand tons/yr)
description: This map depicts the thousands of tons of fruit crops that are grown annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2010.

name: GAP Ecological Systems
description: The GAP (Gap Anlaysis Program) Ecological Systems data layer, one of several data layers available in the U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) GAP Land Cover Dataset, depicts native vegetation, agricultural areas, and urban development in 590 land use classes. Ecological Systems refers to the vegetation classification developed by NatureServe to map the natural vegetation of the U.S. Separate Ecological Systems datasets have been created for Alaska (LANDFIRE) and Hawaii (Hawaii Gap Analysis Project).

name: GAP Status Code (Land Protection Status (GAP))
description: This map depicts protected areas, defined as lands dedicated to and actively managed for the preservation of biological diversity, recreation, and cultural uses, from the U.S. Protected Areas Database (PADUS). The protected lands in this map are categorized according to USGS Gap Analysis Program (GAP) Status Code.

name: General Land Ownership (PADUS)
description: This map depicts protected areas, defined as lands dedicated to and actively managed for the preservation of biological diversity, recreation, and cultural uses, from the U.S. Protected Areas Database (PADUS). The protected lands in this map are categorized according to the type of agency that manages the area.

name: Grain yields (thousand tons/yr)
description: This map depicts the thousands of tons of major grain crops that are grown annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2007-2010.

name: Green space per capita (m2/person)
description: This map illustrates the square meters of total land per person within each census block group that is covered by vegetation, or “green space.”  Green space may include trees, lawns and gardens, crop land, and forested wetlands.

name: Groundwater recharge (m/yr)
description: This map estimates the total long-term average contribution to groundwater recharge in meters/year across each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2000-2013. It reflects water entering the ground from a given cell, without accounting for subsurface groundwater flow. It is the remainder of precipitation that was not accounted for by evapotranspiration or quick flow.

name: Hazardous Waste Sites (RCRA)
description: This dataset includes data from facilities reporting to EPA - Hazardous Waste: Shows points from the RCRAINFO (Resource Conservation and Recovery Act Information) program (All points, Active sites, Inactive sites, Large Quantity Generators (LQG), Transporters, and Treaters, Storers, and Disposers (TSD)). Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: Hazardous Waste Sites (RCRA) - Active
description: This dataset includes data from facilities reporting to EPA - Hazardous Waste: Shows points from the RCRAINFO (Resource Conservation and Recovery Act Information) program for active sites. Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: Hazardous Waste Sites (RCRA) - Inactive
description: This dataset includes data from facilities reporting to EPA - Hazardous Waste: Shows points from the RCRAINFO (Resource Conservation and Recovery Act Information) program for inactive sites. Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: Hazardous Waste Sites (RCRA) - Large Quantity Generators (LQG)
description: This dataset includes data from facilities reporting to EPA - Hazardous Waste: Shows points from the RCRAINFO (Resource Conservation and Recovery Act Information) program for Large Quantity Generators. Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: Hazardous Waste Sites (RCRA) - Transporters
description: This dataset includes data from facilities reporting to EPA - Hazardous Waste: Shows points from the RCRAINFO (Resource Conservation and Recovery Act Information) program for Transporters. Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: Hazardous Waste Sites (RCRA) - Treaters, Storers, and Disposers (TSD)
description: This dataset includes data from facilities reporting to EPA - Hazardous Waste: Shows points from the RCRAINFO (Resource Conservation and Recovery Act Information) program for Treaters, Storers, and Disposers (TSD). Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: Hectares of cotton crops
description: This map depicts the total hectares managed for cotton crops annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2007-2010.

name: Hectares of fruit crops
description: This map depicts the total hectares managed for fruit crops annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2010.

name: Hectares of grain crops
description: This map depicts the total hectares managed for major grain crops annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2007-2010.

name: Hectares of vegetable crops
description: This map depicts the total hectares managed for vegetable crops annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2010.

name: Horses - Number of heads
description: This map shows the number of heads of horses on operations at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Horses - Number of operations
description: This map shows the number of operations with horses on their property at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Hydrologic Unit Code (HUC) Boundaries and labels
description: NHDPlus V2 Hydrologic Unit Code boundaries and labels

name: Imperiled Species and Habitats - Projects and Markets
description: This dataset contains polygons and points representing the location of markets and projects primarily targeting imperiled species and/or habitat ecosystem services per USACE RIBITS data and Ecosystem Marketplace research. Polygons for projects represent the project footprint (i.e. land area comprising the project site) or area of primary impact. Polygons for markets represent the entire region that shares market infrastructure and rules, or a larger program encompassing many smaller projects, such as habitat exchanges. Points represent the centroids of market and project polygons with the exception of national markets, whose points represent administrative headquarters locations.

name: Impervious area per capita (m2/person)
description: This map estimates the square meters of total land per person within each census block group that is covered by impervious surfaces. Impervious surfaces do not allow the penetration of water and include buildings, roads, and sidewalks.

name: Impervious surface in 0.2% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area - Area (m2)
description: This map depicts the total impervious surface area in square meters in the 0.2% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area in each census block group for 2017.

name: Impervious surface in 0.2% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area - Percent
description: This map depicts the percent of land area that is impervious surface in the 0.2% Annual Chance Flood Hazard land area in each census block group for 2017.

name: Impervious surface in 1% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area - Area (m2)
description: This map depicts the total impervious surface area in square meters in the 1% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area in each census block group for 2017.

name: Impervious surface in 1% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area - Percent
description: This map depicts the percent of land area that is impervious surface in the 1% Annual Chance Flood Hazard land area in each census block group for 2017.

name: Industrial water use (million gallons/day)
description: This map estimates the millions of gallons of water used daily for industrial processes in each subwatershed (HUC-12) for 2010. For the purposes of this metric, industrial water use includes chemical, food, paper, wood, and metal production. The industrial water is for self-supplied only such as by private wells or reservoirs. Sources include either surface water or groundwater.

name: Integrated Compliance Information System-Air (ICIS-Air)
description: This dataset contains location and facility identification information from EPA's Facility Registry Service (FRS) for the subset of facilities that link to the Integrated Compliance Information System for Air (AIR). ICIS-Air (AIR) – AIR is the modernization of the Air Facility System (AFS) into the Integrated Compliance Information System (ICIS) and contains compliance and permit data for stationary sources of air pollution (such as electric power plants, steel mills, factories, and universities) regulated by EPA, state and local air pollution agencies. This data set contains the subset of FRS facilities that link to ICIS-Air (AIR) facilities once the ICIS-Air (AIR) data has been fully integrated into the FRS database. Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: Integrated Compliance Information System-Air Major (ICIS-Air Major)
description: This dataset contains location and facility identification information from EPA's Facility Registry Service (FRS) for the subset of facilities that link to dischargers of air pollutants from the Integrated Compliance Information System for Air (AIR). AIR contains enforcement, compliance, and permit data for stationary sources of air pollution regulated by the EPA, State, and Local air pollution agencies. A facility is classified as a Major Discharger if: a) Actual or potential emissions are above the applicable major source thresholds, or b) Actual or potential controlled emissions > 100 tons/year as per Alabama power decision, or c) Unregulated pollutant actual or potential controlled emissions > 100 tons/year as per Alabama power decision. This data set contains the subset of FRS integrated facilities that link to ICIS-Air (AIR) major facilities once the ICIS-Air (AIR) data has been integrated into the FRS database. Updated as source data is updated, typically monthly.

name: IUCN Category (Land Protection Status (IUCN))
description: This map depicts protected areas, defined as lands dedicated to and actively managed for the preservation of biological diversity, recreation, and cultural uses, from the U.S. Protected Areas Database (PADUS). The protected lands in this map are categorized according to International Union for the Conservation of Nature (IUCN) management categories for protected areas.

name: Jobs within a 45-minute drive, weighted
description: This map indicates the relative accessibility to jobs from residences via automobile (in terms of street network travel time) for each census block group, compared to other block groups in the same metropolitan region. Jobs in nearby block groups (based on travel time) are weighted more heavily than those further away.

name: K-12 schools with < 25 percent green space in viewshed
description: This map summarizes the number of K-12 schools in each census block group that have less than 25 percent of “green space” in the area within 100 meters of the building. Green space may include trees, lawns and gardens, crop land, and forested wetlands.

name: Land area in 0.2% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area - Area (m2)
description: This map depicts the total land area in in square meters in the  0.2% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area in each census block group for 2017.

name: Land area in 0.2% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area - Percent
description: This map depicts the percent of land area that is in the 0.2% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area in each census block group for 2017.

name: Land area in 1% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area - Area (m2)
description: This map depicts the total land area in square meters in the 1% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area in each census block group for 2017.

name: Land area in 1% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area - Percent
description: This map depicts the percent of land area that is in the 1% Annual Chance Flood Hazard area in each census block group for 2017.

name: Land cover (Community)
description: The 1-meter resolution land cover map provides a detailed view of the urban environment for analysis of multiple human and ecosystem health metrics and services summarized by U.S. Census block group. Greenspace and impervious surface land cover classes figure prominently.

name: Landscape Conservation Cooperatives
description: Landscape Conservation Cooperatives (LCCs) are represented in this map by 22 regions established across the U.S., Alaska, Hawaii, and U.S. territories. LCC groups are created through conservation and science partnerships between federal agencies, states, tribes, non-governmental organizations, universities, and private stakeholders.

name: Laying hens - Number of heads
description: This map shows the number of heads of laying hens on operations at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Laying hens - Number of operations
description: This map shows the number of operations with laying hens on their property at the end of 2017 by county.

name: Lead air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)
description: This map estimates ambient concentration (microgram/m3) of lead from the National Air Toxics Assessment.

name: Lead air toxics - Neurological risk
description: This map estimates non-cancer neurological risk (hazard quotient) due to lead air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. A hazard quotient is defined as the ratio of the potential exposure to the substance and the level at which no adverse effects are expected. A hazard quotient less than or equal to one indicates that adverse noncancer effects are not likely to occur, and thus can be considered to have negligible hazard.

name: Manure application (kg N/ha/yr)
description: This map depicts the mean rate of manure application to agricultural lands from confined animal feeding operations within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kg N/ha/yr for 2006.

name: Maximum amphibian species richness
description: This map models the maximum number of amphibian species that are likely to be present in any single location within a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The maximum number does not represent the potential richness for the entire watershed.

name: Maximum big game species richness
description: This map models the maximum number of big game species that are likely to be present in any single location within a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The maximum number does not represent the potential richness for the entire watershed.

The maximum number does not represent the potential richness for the entire watershed.

name: MSPA connectivity with water as background and 30-meter edge width for the conterminous United States
description: This EnviroAtlas dataset categorizes land cover into structural elements such as core, edge, or connector. Water is treated as background in this dataset, and edges have a width of 1 pixel (30 meters).

name: MSPA connectivity with water as background and 90-meter edge width for the conterminous United States
description: This EnviroAtlas dataset categorizes land cover into structural elements such as core, edge, or connector. Water is treated as background in this dataset, and edges have a width of 3 pixels (90 meters).

name: MSPA connectivity with water as foreground and 30-meter edge width for the conterminous United States
description: This EnviroAtlas dataset categorizes land cover into structural elements such as core, edge, or connector. Water is treated as foreground in this dataset, and edges have a width of 1 pixel (30 meters).

name: MSPA connectivity with water as foreground and 90-meter edge width for the conterminous United States
description: This EnviroAtlas dataset categorizes land cover into structural elements such as core, edge, or connector. Water is treated as foreground in this dataset, and edges have a width of 3 pixels (90 meters).

name: MSPA connectivity with water as missing and 30-meter edge width for the conterminous United States
description: This EnviroAtlas dataset categorizes land cover into structural elements such as core, edge, or connector. Water is treated as missing in this dataset, and edges have a width of 1 pixel (30 meters).

name: MSPA connectivity with water as missing and 90-meter edge width for the conterminous United States
description: This EnviroAtlas dataset categorizes land cover into structural elements such as core, edge, or connector. Water is treated as missing in this dataset, and edges have a width of 3 pixels (90 meters).

name: Naphthalene air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)
description: This map estimates ambient concentration (microgram/m3) of naphthalene from the National Air Toxics Assessment.

name: Naphthalene air toxics - Cancer risk per million
description: This map estimates cancer risk per million due to naphthalene air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. Cancer risk is defined as the probability of contracting cancer over the course of a lifetime, assuming continuous exposure (assumed in NATA to be 70 years).
ViewName: Naphthalene air toxics - Cancer risk per million

name: Naphthalene air toxics - Respiratory risk (hazard quotient)
description: This map estimates non-cancer respiratory risk (hazard quotient) due to naphthalene air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. A hazard quotient is defined as the ratio of the potential exposure to the substance and the level at which no adverse effects are expected. A hazard quotient less than or equal to one indicates that adverse noncancer effects are not likely to occur, and thus can be considered to have negligible hazard.
ViewName: Naphthalene air toxics - Respiratory risk (hazard quotient)

name: National Land Cover Database (NLCD 2019 Conterminous US Only)
description: NLCD (National Land Cover Database) classifications are based primarily on Landsat data along with ancillary data sources, such as topography, census and agricultural statistics, soil characteristics, wetlands, and other land cover maps. NLCD 2019 is a 16-class land cover classification scheme that has been applied consistently across the conterminous U.S. at a spatial resolution of 30 meters. For additional information, go to https://www.mrlc.gov/. See https://viewer.nationalmap.gov/help for assistance with The National Map viewer, services, or metadata.

name: Native aquatic species rarity index
description: This index averages the rarity for native aquatic species within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). Species rarity is based on species range, with species with smaller ranges being more rare. The data is based on IUCN ranges for fish, amphibians, mollusks, turtles, and crustaceans (shrimp and crayfish).

name: Native aquatic species richness
description: This map estimates the number of native aquatic animal species – including fish, amphibians, mollusks, turtles, and crustaceans (shrimp and crayfish) – present within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). The number of species present was estimated based on species range data from IUCN.

name: Native aquatic species vulnerability index
description: This map depicts a native aquatic species vulnerability index for each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). Vulnerability is based on both the threatened and endangered status and rarity of species. The data is based on IUCN ranges for fish, amphibians, mollusks, turtles, and crustaceans (shrimp and crayfish).

name: Natural biological nitrogen fixation (kg N/ha/yr)
description: This map depicts mean biological nitrogen fixation in natural and semi-natural ecosystems within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in kg N/ha/yr for 2006.

name: Net agricultural phosphorus balance (kg P/ha/yr)
description: This map estimates the mean phosphorus (P) balance between P inputs on croplands from inorganic fertilizer and manure, and removal of P by crops in kilograms P per hectare per year within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2012.

name: NHDPlus V2 features
description: NHDPlus V2 features for waterbodies, areas, and flowlines. Flowlines are displayed based on Stream Order and Stream Order 1 features are not displayed in this service.

name: NIB amphibian species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of amphibian species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB big game species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of big game species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB bird species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of bird species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB common bird species in steep decline
description: This map depicts an index value of the richness of species listed by Partners in Flight as common species in steep decline for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC
ViewName: NIB common bird species in steep decline

name: NIB fur bearer species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of fur bearer species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB mammal species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of mammal species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB modeled G1, G2, G3 terrestrial vertebrate species
description: This map depicts an index value of NatureServe Globally Ranked Terrestrial Vertebrate Species (G1, G2, and G3) richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. G1 species are critically imperiled, G2 species are imperiled, and G3 species are vulnerable. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.
ViewName: NIB modeled G1, G2, G3 terrestrial vertebrate species

name: NIB modeled IUCN threatened terrestrial vertebrate species
description: This map depicts an index value of International Union for Conservation of Nature (IUCN)-listed endangered species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.
ViewName: NIB modeled IUCN threatened terrestrial vertebrate species

name: NIB modeled Partners in Amphibian and Reptile Conservation (PARC) species
description: This map depicts an index value of Partners in Amphibian and Reptile Conservation (PARC) species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. These species are listed as either threatened and endangered, G1-G3 or IUCN. G1 species are critically imperiled, G2 species are imperiled, and G3 species are vulnerable. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.
ViewName: NIB modeled Partners in Amphibian and Reptile Conservation (PARC) species

name: NIB modeled Partners in Flight Watch List bird species
description: This map depicts an index value of bird species richness for bird species listed by Partners in Flight in their Watch List for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC. The Partners in Flight Watch List Normalized Index of Biodiversity (NIB) was calculated by dividing the mean species richness value of each HUC by the maximum value for the study area.
ViewName: NIB modeled Partners in Flight Watch List bird species

name: NIB modeled State of the Birds species of conservation concern
description: This map depicts an index value of bird species richness for Birds of Conservation Concern for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC. The Birds of Conservation Concern Normalized Index of Biodiversity (NIB) was calculated by dividing the mean species richness value of each HUC by the maximum value for the study area.
ViewName: NIB modeled State of the Birds species of conservation concern

name: NIB modeled threatened and endangered vertebrate species
description: This map depicts an index value of Endangered Species Act threatened and endangered species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.
ViewName: NIB modeled threatened and endangered vertebrate species

name: NIB number of bird species vulnerable to range loss due to climate change by 2050
description: This map depicts an index value of Audubon Climate Endangered bird species (http://climate.audubon.org/) richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. These are bird species vulnerable to a loss of 50% or more of current range due to climate change by 2050. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.
ViewName: NIB number of bird species vulnerable to range loss due to climate change by 2050

name: NIB number of bird species vulnerable to range loss due to climate change by 2080
description: This map depicts an index value of Audubon Climate Threatened bird species (http://climate.audubon.org/) richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. These are bird species vulnerable to a loss of 50% or more of current range due to climate change by 2080. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.
ViewName: NIB number of bird species vulnerable to range loss due to climate change by 2080

name: NIB rare amphibian species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of rare amphibian species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. Rare species were the 25% of amphibian species with the smallest amount of predicted habitat. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB rare bird species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of rare bird species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. Rare species were the 25% of bird species with the smallest amount of predicted habitat. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB rare mammal species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of rare mammal species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. Rare species were the 25% of mammal species with the smallest amount of predicted habitat. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB rare reptile species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of rare reptile species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. Rare species were the 25% of reptile species with the smallest amount of predicted habitat. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB rare vertebrate species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of rare terrestrial vertebrate species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. Rare species were the 25% of vertebrate species with the smallest amount of predicted habitat. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB small game species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of small game species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB summer bird species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of bird species richness during the summer for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB total harvestable species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of harvestable species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB total vertebrate species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of vertebrate species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB waterfowl species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of waterfowl species richness for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: NIB winter bird species richness
description: This map depicts an index value of bird species richness during the winter for a subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in the Conterminous US for 2001. This map is based on habitat models, not wildlife observations. The index value is based on average values determined for each HUC.

name: Nitrate violation index - Groundwater
description: This map represents the random forest probability of a nitrate violation for groundwater systems. Higher values indicate a higher probability of a risk of violation. A random forest model is an ensemble of many decision trees, with the probability indicating the proportion of trees predicting a violation. Based on violations occuring between 2013 and 2017.

name: Nitrate violation index - Surface water
description: This map represents the random forest probability of a nitrate violation for surface water systems. Higher values indicate a higher probability of a risk of violation. A random forest model is an ensemble of many decision trees, with the probability indicating the proportion of trees predicting a violation. Based on violations occuring between 2013 and 2017.

name: Nitrogen dioxide removed annually by tree cover (kg/yr)
description: This map estimates the total kilograms of nitrogen dioxide removed annually by trees in each census block group.

name: Non-cancer neurological risk (hazard index) due to cumulative air toxics
description: This map estimates non-cancer neurological risk (hazard quotient) due to cumulative air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment, expressed as a hazard index. A hazard index is defined as, The sum of hazard quotients for toxics that affect the same target organ or organ system. A hazard index (HI) of 1 or lower means air toxics are unlikely to cause adverse noncancer health effects over a lifetime of exposure.
ViewName: Non-cancer neurological risk (hazard index) due to cumulative air toxics

name: Non-native aquatic species richness - animals
description: This map depicts species richness for non-native aquatic animals for each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). It is based on observation data from multiple data sources. Zero does not necessarily imply absence.

name: Non-native aquatic species richness - plants
description: This map depicts species richness for non-native aquatic plants for each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). It is based on observation data from multiple data sources. Zero does not necessarily imply absence.

name: Non-native aquatic species richness - plants and animals
description: This map depicts species richness for non-native aquatic plants and animals for each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). It is based on observation data from multiple data sources. Zero does not necessarily imply absence.
ViewName: Non-native aquatic species richness - plants and animals

name: Non-tile drainage system subsurface water flow from agricultural lands (mm)
description: This map provides modeled estimates of sub-surface (lateral) flow at the outer edges of non-tile drained agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in millimeters (mm) of water for 2002.
ViewName: Non-tile drainage system subsurface water flow from agricultural lands (mm)

name: Number of at-risk aquatic animal species observed
description: This map illustrates the total number of observed animal species associated with aquatic habitat that are listed as G1, G2, or in the federal endangered species program that may reside within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2011. G1 and G2 denote Global Conservation Ranks classified by NatureServe. Zero does not necessarily imply absence.
ViewName: Number of at-risk aquatic animal species observed

name: Number of at-risk aquatic plant species observed
description: This map illustrates the total number of observed plant species associated with aquatic habitat that are listed as G1, G2, or in the federal endangered species program that may reside within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2011. G1 and G2 denote Global Conservation Ranks classified by NatureServe. Zero does not necessarily imply absence.
ViewName: Number of at-risk aquatic plant species observed

name: Number of at-risk terrestrial animal species observed
description: This map illustrates the total number of observed animal species associated with terrestrial habitat that are listed as G1, G2, or in the federal endangered species program that may reside within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2011. G1 and G2 denote Global Conservation Ranks classified by NatureServe. Terrestrial habitat refers to land areas such as forests, grasslands, deserts and rainforests.  Zero does not necessarily imply absence.
ViewName: Number of at-risk terrestrial animal species observed

name: Number of at-risk terrestrial plant species observed
description: This map illustrates the total number of observed plant species associated with terrestrial habitat that are listed as G1, G2, or in the federal endangered species program that may reside within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2011. G1 and G2 denote Global Conservation Ranks classified by NatureServe. Terrestrial habitat refers to land areas such as forests, grasslands, deserts and rainforests.  Zero does not necessarily imply absence.
ViewName: Number of at-risk terrestrial plant species observed

name: Number of at-risk wetland animal species observed
description: This map illustrates the total number of observed animal species associated with wetland habitat that are listed as G1, G2, or in the federal endangered species program that may reside within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2011. G1 and G2 denote Global Conservation Ranks classified by NatureServe. Zero does not necessarily imply absence.
ViewName: Number of at-risk wetland animal species observed

name: Number of at-risk wetland plant species observed
description: This map illustrates the total number of observed plant species associated with wetland habitat that are listed as G1, G2, or in the federal endangered species program that may reside within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2011. G1 and G2 denote Global Conservation Ranks classified by NatureServe. Zero does not necessarily imply absence.
ViewName: Number of at-risk wetland plant species observed

name: Number of combined sewer overflow events
description: The total number of reported combined sewer overflow events (CSOs) at publicly-owned treatment works located in the watershed in 2009. (Source: ICIS-NPDES)
ViewName: Number of combined sewer overflow events

name: Number of day care centers
description: This map shows the number of day care centers in each census block group.

name: Number of farmers markets [12-digit HUC]
description: This map depicts the number of farmers markets within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2016.

name: Number of farmers markets [census block group]
description: This map depicts the number of farmers markets within each census block group for 2016.
ViewName: Number of farmers markets [census block group]

name: Number of fruit crop types (annually)
description: This map depicts the number of fruit crop types that are grown annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2010.

name: Number of grain crop types (annually)
description: This map depicts the number of major grain crop types that are grown annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2007-2010.

name: Number of high hazard potential dams
description: This map depicts the number of high hazard potential dams within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). For this map, EnviroAtlas uses the 2009 National Inventory of Dams maintained by the US Army Corps of Engineers.
ViewName: Number of high hazard potential dams

name: Number of high-wage workers [work location]
description: This map estimates the number of workers earning more than $3333 per month summarized by workplace location within each census block group.

name: Number of historic places
description: This map summarizes the number of federally listed historic districts, sites, buildings, structures, and objects within each census block group.

name: Number of historic places [census block group]
description: This map summarizes the number of federally listed historic districts, sites, buildings, structures, and objects within each census block group.

name: Number of households
description: This map illustrates the number of households (i.e., occupied housing units) within each census block group in 2010. A household consists of all people who occupy a housing unit regardless of relationship. See user guide for details: https:

name: Number of households with zero vehicles
description: This map illustrates the number of households without vehicles within each census block group in 2010. The word vehicle refers to private motor vehicles such as cars and trucks.
ViewName: Number of households with zero vehicles

name: Number of low-wage workers [home location]
description: This map estimates the number of workers earning $1250 or less per month summarized by residence within each census block group.

name: Number of low-wage workers [work location]
description: This map estimates the number of workers earning $1250 or less per month summarized by workplace location within each census block group.

name: Number of middle-wage workers [work location]
description: This map estimates the number of workers earning between $1250 and $3333 per month summarized by workplace location within each census block group.

name: Number of schools (K-12)
description: This map shows the number of K-12 schools in each census block group.

name: Number of vegetable crop types (annually)
description: This map depicts the number of vegetable crop types that are grown annually within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2010.

name: Number of vulnerable native aquatic species based on IUCN range
description: This map depicts the number of native aquatic animal species – including fish, amphibians, mollusks, turtles, and crustaceans (shrimp and crayfish) – that were listed as "vulnerable," "endangered," or "critically endangered" by the IUCN Red List within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). The number of species present was estimated based on species habitat range data from IUCN.
ViewName: Number of vulnerable native aquatic species based on IUCN range

name: Number of workers [home location]
description: This map illustrates the total number of workers by home location in 2010 within each census block group.

name: Nutrients attached to eroding surface soil from agricultural fields (tons) Nitrogen
description: This map provides modeled estimates of the movement (flux) of nitrogen attached to soil particles eroding from the surface of the agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of N for 2002. It includes nitrogen from fertilizer application and atmospheric deposition.
ViewName: Nutrients attached to eroding surface soil from agricultural fields (tons) Nitrogen

name: Nutrients attached to eroding surface soil from agricultural fields (tons) Phosphorus
description: This map provides modeled estimates of the movement (flux) of phosphorus attached to soil particles eroding from the surface of the agricultural fields within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) in metric tons of P for 2002. It includes phosphorus from fertilizer application and atmospheric deposition.
ViewName: Nutrients attached to eroding surface soil from agricultural fields (tons) Phosphorus

name: Ozone removed annually by tree cover (kg/yr)
description: This map estimates the total kilograms of ozone removed annually by trees in each census block group.

name: PAH / POM air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)
description: This map estimates ambient concentration (microgram/m3) of polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (PAH) / polycyclic organic matter (POM) from the National Air Toxics Assessment.
ViewName: PAH / POM air toxics - Ambient concentration (μg/m3)

name: PAH / POM air toxics - Cancer risk per million
description: This map estimates cancer risk per million due to polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons (PAH) / polycyclic organic matter (POM) air toxics from the National Air Toxics Assessment. Cancer risk is defined as the probability of contracting cancer over the course of a lifetime, assuming continuous exposure (assumed in NATA to be 70 years).
ViewName: PAH / POM air toxics - Cancer risk per million

name: Particulate matter [PM10] removed annually by tree cover (kg/yr)
description: This map estimates the total kilograms of particulate matter greater than 2.5 microns but less than 10 microns that is removed annually by trees in each census block group.

name: Particulate matter [PM2.5] removed annually by tree cover (kg/yr)
description: This map estimates the total kilograms of particulate matter less than 2.5 microns that are removed annually by trees in each census block group.

name: Pedestrian-oriented street intersection density (intersections per square mile)
description: This map estimates the degree of pedestrian-oriented street connectivity for each census block group, measured as street intersections per square mile. Intersections that exclude pedestrian passage were not counted.
ViewName: Pedestrian-oriented street intersection density (intersections per square mile)

name: Percent agriculture on hydric soil
description: This map depicts the percentage of land managed for agriculture that has hydric soils within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) for 2006-2010. This includes all land dedicated to the production of crops, but excludes land managed for pasture.

name: Percent agriculture
description: This map estimates the percent of total land within each census block group that is managed for agriculture.

name: Percent carbon monoxide removed annually by tree cover
description: This map estimates the mean percent of carbon monoxide removed annually by tree cover in each census block group.

name: Percent cropland
description: This map depicts the percent of land managed as cropland in each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). For cropland classifications, the conterminous US is based on the EnviroAtlas 2019 National Land Cover Database; Alaska is based on the 2016 National Land Cover Database; Hawaii is based on 2005-2011 NOAA Coastal Change Analysis Program (C-CAP) data; Puerto Rico is based on 2010 NOAA C-CAP data; and the US Virgin Islands is based on 2012 NOAA C-CAP data.

name: Percent cropland on slopes >= 3%
description: Percentage of land area within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that is classified as cropland on areas with slopes greater than or equal to three percent.
ViewName: Percent cropland on slopes greater than or equal to 3%

name: Percent cropland on slopes >= 9%
description: Percentage of land area within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that is classified as cropland on areas with slopes greater than or equal to nine percent.
ViewName: Percent cropland on slopes greater than or equal to 9%

name: Percent developed area
description: This map estimates the amount of developed land within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). For the purposes of this map, developed land cover includes a variety of development, such as single family homes, multifamily housing units, retail, commercial, industrial sites, and associated infrastructure. Developed land cover is not confined to city limits. For land use/land cover classifications, the conterminous US is based on the EnviroAtlas 2019 National Land Cover Database; Alaska is based on the 2016 National Land Cover Database; Hawaii is based on 2005-2011 NOAA Coastal Change Analysis Program (C-CAP) data; Puerto Rico is based on 2010 NOAA C-CAP data; and the US Virgin Islands is based on 2012 NOAA C-CAP data.

name: Percent emergent herbaceous wetlands
description: This map depicts the percentage of land comprised of emergent herbaceous wetlands in each subwatershed (12-digit HUC). For land use/land cover classifications, the conterminous US is based on the EnviroAtlas 2019 National Land Cover Database; Alaska is based on the 2016 National Land Cover Database; Hawaii is based on 2005-2011 NOAA Coastal Change Analysis Program (C-CAP) data; Puerto Rico is based on 2010 NOAA C-CAP data; and the US Virgin Islands is based on 2012 NOAA C-CAP data.

name: Percent forest
description: This map illustrates the percentage of total land within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that is covered by trees and forest. For land use/land cover classifications, the conterminous US is based on the EnviroAtlas 2019 National Land Cover Database; Alaska is based on the 2016 National Land Cover Database; Hawaii is based on 2005-2011 NOAA Coastal Change Analysis Program (C-CAP) data; Puerto Rico is based on 2010 NOAA C-CAP data; and the US Virgin Islands is based on 2012 NOAA C-CAP data.

name: Percent forest and woody wetlands
description: This map illustrates the percentage of total land within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that is covered by trees and forest or woody wetlands. For land use/land cover classifications, the conterminous US is based on the EnviroAtlas 2019 National Land Cover Database; Alaska is based on the 2016 National Land Cover Database; Hawaii is based on 2005-2011 NOAA Coastal Change Analysis Program (C-CAP) data; Puerto Rico is based on 2010 NOAA C-CAP data; and the US Virgin Islands is based on 2012 NOAA C-CAP data.

name: Percent forest and woody wetlands in stream buffer
description: This map layer portrays the percent of land within 45 meters of streams, rivers, and other hydrologically connected waterbodies within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that is covered by trees and forests or woody wetlands. For land use/land cover classifications, the conterminous US is based on the EnviroAtlas 2016 Cropland Data Layer-National Land Cover Database hybrid; Alaska is based on the 2016 National Land Cover Database; Hawaii is based on 2005-2011 NOAA Coastal Change Analysis Program (C-CAP) data; Puerto Rico is based on 2010 NOAA C-CAP data; and the US Virgin Islands is based on 2012 NOAA C-CAP data.
ViewName: Percent forest and woody wetlands in stream buffer

name: Percent forest land in stream buffer
description: This map layer portrays the percent of land within 45 meters of streams, rivers, and other hydrologically connected waterbodies within each subwatershed (12-digit HUC) that is covered by trees and forests.
